    # [Scene: Municipal Plaza | Early Fall, Late Afternoon]

    scene bg ch15_f7128a_1 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Taut strings underpinned by rapid percussion; urgency humming]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: A distant legal bell—phone alerts, muted voices trialing off]
    "You stand beneath a taut banner—letters for 'AUDIT NOW' half-hidden by rain. The decision you made in the council chamber hangs on your bones like cold. You remember telling the room, hours and court filings ago,"
    "that transparency was worth the delay; that an independent audit would catch the clauses designed to swallow the town whole. You remember the way Mateo's hand tightened into yours when you spoke."
    "Now the delay has teeth. The town's calendar has been rewritten into court dates, depositions, and provisional injunctions. The investors blinked. The firm's lawyers filed counterclaims. The campaign that rallied early has frayed into spokes of"
    "fatigue: volunteers juggling day jobs, kids' schedules, two-hour commutes, and endless paperwork. Mara's recorder is warm in your tote; her face, when she finds you, is drained but fierce."
    show mara_chen at left:
        zoom 0.7

    mara_chen "You know what the feeds are saying?"
    show ari_tanaka at right:
        zoom 0.7

    ari_tanaka "Half the feeds. Half the truth. What are you hearing?"

    mara_chen "The headline is 'Town Delays Protections.' Framing: obstruction. My piece needs the audit transcripts, Ari. Etta's notes gave me leads, but—' (she knocks the recorder against her palm) '—we have to be precise. They—Elio's crowd—are burying the context under 'delay equals risk.'"
    "You nod, throat pinched. The word 'risk' now rides the sentences of strangers who don't feel the salt in their lungs."
    hide mara_chen
    hide ari_tanaka

    scene bg ch15_f7128a_2 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Low, insistent electronic throb]
    show mara_chen at left:
        zoom 0.7

    mara_chen "If the audit isn't released, the narrative hardens. We need the public to understand why 'pause' was the only ethical call."
    show ari_tanaka at right:
        zoom 0.7

    ari_tanaka "We need people to feel what we feel—let them see the clause language, not the press-spin. Get me the community statements. I'll take them to the lab; Mateo can collate sensor logs. Etta—' (you think of the greenhouse, of its warm amber light) '—Etta can keep the nursery a place people come to breathe."

    mara_chen "You're still trying to stitch breath into policy, huh. All right—I'll dig. But Ari—' (she steps closer; her voice drops) '—don't let the slow grind hollow you."
    "You swallow. The plaza is full of faces that once listened and now argue about logistics. You can feel the arousal: the sharp, nervous energy like a storm under the skin. You will not let this be calm."
    # [Scene: Wave Innovation Lab | Early Evening]
    hide mara_chen
    hide ari_tanaka

    scene bg ch15_f7128a_3 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Beeping monitors; distant wind against the pilings]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Percussive tension; a high string tremor]
    "Mateo Alvarez is bent over a set of buoys, gloved hands precise as if the world will be fixed by torque alone. When he looks up, there's a line between his brows you haven't erased in weeks."
    show mateo_alvarez at left:
        zoom 0.7

    mateo_alvarez "They sent another subpoena. They're asking for our meeting notes from last spring."
    show ari_tanaka at right:
        zoom 0.7

    ari_tanaka "They have no right—"

    mateo_alvarez "Right. But they also have pockets deep enough to drown the rest of us in delays. Each legal day is a day without reinforced pilings. Each injunction makes the shore softer."

    ari_tanaka "We asked for transparency and time to negotiate fair terms. We didn't ask for—"

    mateo_alvarez "You didn't ask for lawsuits, Ari. You asked for audits.' (he pulls a coil of sensor cable taut between two callused fingers) 'But audits turn into hearings when interests are threatened. We can document everything—we can—' (he exhales). 'I keep thinking about the pilot schedule. If this drags on, we can't simulate the buoy response before winter storms. We can't scale."
    "You study him. He's an architect of compromise, but now his patience is brittle. The lab's LEDs blink like nervous eyes."

    mateo_alvarez "I need you to understand—if we don't move on construction soon, funding dries. The investors are waiting for assurances that a machine will be in the water. The board wants results."

    ari_tanaka "And we want safeguards before results are promised at any cost. We owe the town that."

    mateo_alvarez "I get it. But I can't stand by while we watch the sea take people because we were proving a point. Help me find a middle that keeps our integrity and gets hardware in the water."
    "Ari Tanaka: (you feel the old reflex—protect everyone, weigh every loss) 'If we contrive a middle, it must include binding covenants—no buyouts, no privatized access, and a public oversight board with veto power in emergencies.'"

    mateo_alvarez "And if they don't agree?' (a beat) 'Then—"

    menu:
        "Call Etta and ask her to open the greenhouse all night":
            "You pull your phone, thumb hovering. The idea of Etta's warm light is an anchor. You imagine the nursery as a shelter for trembling volunteers, and feel a small, stubborn relief."
        "Compile sensor logs to send to Mara first":
            "You tap through the lab's data, watching tidal graphs spike. Sending hard data feels like sending a stake into an argument. You feel purposeful, but the clock keeps clicking."

